          From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia                            Jump to:     navigation,      search          Complexa is red Portuguese wine grape used in the production of Madeira. The grape was created as a crossing of Castelao, Muscat Hamburg and Tintinha in the 1960s. The grape provides a deep color with less tannins than the commonly used Tinta Negra Mole.[1] See also[edit]  List of Portuguese grape varieties  References[edit]   ^ J. Robinson (ed) "The Oxford Companion to Wine" Third Edition pg 191 Oxford University Press 2006 ISBN 0-19-860990-6      This wine grape-related article is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it.   v t e                         Retrieved from "https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Complexa&oldid=582627154"          Categories: Red wine grape varietiesMadeira wineWine grape stubsHidden categories: All stub articles            
